Is there any advantage in your mind to keeping our test or UAT =
environments on a local device =E2=80=93 or should we move all to AWS?=20

C

=20

From: Josh Klein <josh@josh.is>=20
Sent: 27 May 2020 17:55
To: Chris at Indigo <chris@indigometrics.com>
Subject: AWS + security

=20

The more I read about the way AWS is set up the more comfortable I feel =
with setting up a VM. They have plenty of security group permissioning =
capabilities, such that we can limit access from a particular client to =
only connect from predesignated IPs, etc. Their log monitoring platform =
seems pretty comprehensive. And their at-rest encryption should address =
any data storage concerns (as Misha said.)=20

=20

In other words, I think that if we move solely to a VM instance, use =
best practices for permissioning, and put some good log monitoring in =
place I'm not certain we'll need a SIDS HIDS or NIDS. Moreover, if we =
move the client instance to LAMBDA instead of a hosted solution we may =
be able to avoid ongoing patching regimes as well.=20

=20

Food for thought,

Josh

